Karenina
Out of my way!
Karenina keeps dodging the incoming gravitational waves and knocking the Corrupted away.

In less than an hour's time, the gravitational waves are affecting a smaller radius but with significantly greater intensity. Some of the buildings in the lunar base are already decomposed into large debris.
After another huge explosion, blazing blue light begins to emit from debris and dust.
Karenina
The zero-point engine... is right over there!
The spherical zero-point engine is engulfed in a gravity storm, sucking in all nearby debris, lunar soil and the limbs of Corrupted. The anti-gravity field slowly lifts the engine into the sky.
Karenina
All the gravitational waves are concentrating in the engine... I can't waste any more time here.
Karenina slams the Blast Hammer hard on the Moon's surface. She keeps boosting the pressure in the hammer's propulsion engine.
Estimating gravity... Trajectory simulation complete. Engine compression 100%... 120%!
Karenina
If I can't get there from the ground, I'll just go from above!
Assets/Product/Effect/Prefab/FxUi/FxUiStoryNew/FxUiStoryFallNew.prefab

When the engine reaches peak power, Karenina pulls the trigger. The charged kinetic energy is immediately released, shattering the fragile moon rocks underneath and launching Karenina along with the hammer rapidly toward her destination.
Assets/Product/Texture/Image/BgStory/BgStory594.jpg
Assets/Product/Texture/Image/BgStory/BgStory594.jpg
The gravity control device in her frame and the Blast Hammer's propulsion allow Karenina to adjust her stance while airborne, nimbly avoiding the impact of gravitational waves.
But she soon finds out that whenever she tries to approach the zero-point engine, the gravitational waves would be in her way as if they are directly aimed at her.
Karenina
How strange... I feel like the zero-point engine has its own consciousness. It is trying to push me away.
After dodging another round of dense gravitational waves, Karenina transforms the Blast Hammer into the cannon form and fires at the zero-point engine.
PanelActor1Shake
PanelActor1Shake
The engine immediately compresses the gravitational waves to neutralize her shot. This is definitely not a coincidence.
Karenina
It's impossible! How can the zero-point engine protect itself...? Unless...

Karenina keeps firing at the gravity storm around the zero-point engine. When she finally peels off the debris, she finds some pale matter entangled at the bottom of the engine and is continuously growing upward.
It is not lunar soil or shattered debris, but a creature that she has never seen.
PanelActor1Shake
PanelActor1Shake
Slightly distracted, Karenina is hit by gravitational waves and falls to the Moon's surface. Thanks to the low gravity, she has not suffered much damage.

Karenina
Cough... ****! What the **** was that...?
Karenina has never seen such a creepy scene. When the pale matter finally wraps the zero-point engine within, the gravity storm gradually calms down. Everything seems to have stopped.
All of a sudden, the zero-point engine on top starts to shake vigorously. The crack on its pale outer shell turns to Karenina and "stares" at her like a creature's eye.
Karenina's instinct tells her the "creature" is dangerous. Without thinking, she raises her cannon and fires at it.
Karenina
What the?!
The compressed graviton fired from her cannon is blocked by this peculiar piece of flesh—to be precise, by its newly grown "arm."
Soon, the pale flesh quickly grows another arm, followed by two legs. It slowly gets up on its feet and grows into a creepy humanoid.
Pale Mutant
Gargh— Argh—!
Assets/Product/Texture/Image/BgStory/Bgstory428.jpg
Assets/Product/Texture/Image/BgStory/BgStory538.png
Assets/Product/Texture/Image/BgStory/Bgstory428.jpg
Assets/Product/Texture/Image/BgStory/BgStory593.jpg
It lets out a hysterical cry. Uncontrolled gravitational waves burst out, shattering everything around.
Karenina does not need to ask it to know that this creature is her enemy. It's an enemy to all humans!
It continues to drain the energy supplied to the zero-point engine and emits crimson Punishing Virus.
Karenina
Is this freak a Hetero-Creature?
The monster frenetically scratches itself. Blue "blood" full of zero-point energy flows out from its wounds, but the blue color soon fades and is replaced by crimson.
The lunar soil nearby is soaked with this crimson liquid—or the Red Tide, to be more precise.
Pale Mutant
Gargh—!
The wounds left by its claws soon heal themselves. The energy drained from the zero-point engine will repair its body endlessly.
This energy will become an infinite source of the Punishing Virus. Soon, the entire Moon will be covered in the crimson blood color.
Karenina
The zero-point engine must be destroyed... I'll smash you!
Assets/Product/Texture/Image/BgStory/BgStory594.jpg
Like a morning star, a small light dot rises into the deep, silent sky from the back of the Earth, followed by the blazing Sun.
But when looking closer at it, the "star" is blinking at a certain rhythm.
Karenina
Babylonia...!
The blinking navigation lights in Babylonia were once used for communicating with other orbiter spacecraft, but they are too outdated and are no longer in use.
Babylonia has no need to communicate with other orbiter spacecraft—with no other orbital spacecraft left, Babylonia is the only unit that watches the Earth from space.
Right now, the lights are operating once again for just one person. The message is for Karenina and Karenina alone.
Karenina
The World Government... has decided...
Karenina carefully reads the message conveyed in the signal. The decision of humanity awaits her.
Karenina
...to acknowledge and approve... the Engineering Force's decision... Karenina...
Her eyes widen as she gazes at the blinking light, still finding it difficult to believe.
Karenina
...go ahead... and destroy the zero-point engine!
The signals cannot convey complex instructions, but they are more than enough to give Karenina never-ending courage.
She looks up and sniffles to stop the tears, then turns around and gives the monster a fearless smile.
Karenina
Hey, did you hear that? You bloody Punishing monster...
Karenina holds her Blast Hammer up and points it directly at the monster. The tail flames from its propulsion engine are burning strong.
Karenina
They... The humans... want me to crush you.
Even when standing alone in the dark universe, Karenina no longer feels any fear. She knows the will of the entire human race is twinkling behind her, and this undying will—
—will become a star... and a torch.
Karenina
So... Just ******* die!
